cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper is about a large-scale data set of video URLs with densely-sampled object bounding box annotations for object detection in video. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep network architectures for classification and localization, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the potential use of temporal contiguity of video for improving inferences, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
